  "prompt": "How do I maximize my running speed?",
  "response": "To maximize your running speed, consider these key strategies:\n\n1. Strength Training\n- Build leg and core muscles\n- Focus on squats, lunges, and plyometrics\n- Improve overall muscle power and explosiveness\n\n2. Proper Technique\n- Maintain good running form\n- Keep head up, shoulders relaxed\n- Drive arms efficiently\n- Land mid-foot, not heel\n- Take shorter, quicker strides\n\n3. Speed Workouts\n- Interval training\n- Sprint repeats\n- Hill sprints\n- Tempo runs\n- Gradually increase intensity and duration\n\n4. Flexibility and Mobility\n- Regular stretching\n- Dynamic warm-ups\n- Improve range of motion\n- Reduce injury risk\n\n5. Cardiovascular Conditioning\n- Consistent aerobic training\n- Improve overall cardiovascular endurance\n- Mix long, slow runs with high-intensity workouts\n\n6. Nutrition\n- Balanced diet with lean protein\n- Complex carbohydrates\n- Adequate hydration\n- Proper pre and post-workout nutrition\n\n7. Rest and Recovery\n- Allow muscle recovery\n- Get sufficient sleep\n- Prevent overtraining\n- Use foam rolling and massage\n\n8. Specific Speed Training\n- Resistance training\n- Parachute or weighted vest running\n- Explosive drills\n\nConsistent practice and gradual progression are key to improving running speed.",
